Logic seems fine here, but naming here seems confusing (`opt_indent` vs `option_indent`) and inconsistent (`msg_indent` vs `para_indent`). Would suggest renames to fix like:

```c++
constexpr int OPTION_INDENT  = 2;
constexpr int MESSAGE_INDENT = 7;
const int option_indent = OPTION_INDENT + (subopt ? MESSAGE_INDENT - OPTION_INDENT : 0);
const int message_indent = MESSAGE_INDENT + (subopt ? MESSAGE_INDENT - OPTION_INDENT : 0);
```

